{
  "stem": "9168.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And somehow that was another shock to me, to have so many found not guilty, or acquitted and released.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I felt maybe there were several who might have been.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now when the defendants-- and I'll never forget this scene-- who were sentenced to death by hanging, each one, including Karl Brandt, stood before the four judge tribunal to hear this sentence, flanked by American MP-- MPs-- military police.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Each one threw the Heil Hitler salute at the judges, clicked the heels of his boots, and turned and arrogantly strode out of that courtroom under guard with his head held high.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was not a sign of any kind of remorse shown.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But after we had heard the testimony and their rationalizations, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in the case of Karl Brandt, his-- he knew he was a doctor, that he had taken the Hippocratic oath.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But he felt that order and obedience took priority.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had received his orders, and it was obedience to those orders.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The charter that was set up took the [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] possibility of their claiming innocence by virtue of following orders into consideration.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And one of the rules in the-- the charter, or the subsequent rules that were set up governing these trials, was that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there could not be a legitimate defense to the following of orders.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--that we reported.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I understood that-- I had the feeling, because I had also talked to judges out of the courtroom.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I knew that there was a feeling on the part of the judges that they wanted to be very careful in trying these cases not to have the world view, these as predetermined trials of revenge, of vengeance.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
